The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the orthogonal range reporting problem. This problem is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions that the results can be used to obtain better solutions for some stringology problems, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG).
